Practice problems:
—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Adam number] 

12 --- 21  | [Accept the input from the user and reverse the number]
 |      |  | 
 |     441 | [take a square of a reversed number] 
 |      |  | 
144 == 144 | [if input² == reversed_(reversed_input²) - [Adam number]]

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Armstrong number] 

    153----| [Accept the input from the user]
   / | \   | 
  1  5  3  | [count the digits and segregate the digits]
  |  |  |  | 
  1+125+27 | [calculate the exponential based on digits count for each digits and do sum]
   \ | /   | 
    153----| [if sum == input [Armstrong number]]

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Strong number]

    145----| [Accept the input from the user]
   / | \   | 
  1  4  5  | [segregate the digits]
  |  |  |  | 
  1+24+120 | [calculate the factorial based on digits and do sum]
   \ | /   | 
    145----| [if sum == input [Strong number]]

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Magic number] 

    1927    | [Accept the input from the user] 
  / |  | \  |  
 1  9  2  7 | [segregate the digits] 
 |  |  |  | | 
 1+ 9+ 2+ 7 | [do sum of all the digits] 
  \ |  | /  |  
    (19)    | [if sum == 1 [Magic]][if 2≤sum≤9 [Not a Magic]][if sum>9 do repeat from step 2] 
   /    \ 
  1      9 
  |      |
  1   +  9 
   \    /
    (10)
   /    \ 
  1      0 
  |      |
  1   +  0 
   \    /
    (01)

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Happy number] 

    82   | [Accept the input from the user]   
   /  \  |     
  8    2 | [Seperate the digits] 
  |    | | 
  64 + 4 | [do the sum of all the digit²] 
   \  /  | 
    68   | [if sum == 1 [happy number]][if 2≤sum≤9 [Not a happy number]][else do repeat from step 2]
   /  \
  6    8 
  |    |
  36 +64 
   \  /
   +100
   / | \
  1  0  0 
  |  |  |
  1 +0 +0 
   \ | / 
    (1)

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––
 
[Kapreker number] 

297² = 88209

8 + 8209 = 8217 
88 + 209 =  297 
882 + 09 =  891 
8820 + 9 = 8829 

if the sum of splitted values of input² == input [Kapreker] 

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Perfect number] 

Sum of the factors of the input (Excluding input) == input

Example., 1)  6 = 1 + 2 + 3 

          2) 28 = 1 + 2 + 4 + 7 + 14

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Extra perfect number]

Number which contains 1's only at the starting and ending of a binary representation

Example., 

11       = 3 
101      = 5 
1001     = 9 
10001    = 17 
100001   = 33 
1000001  = 65 
10000001 = 129

if input == ( 2ⁿ + 1 ) -> [Extra perfect number]

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Abundant number]

Sum of the factors of the input (Excluding input) > input

Example., 1) 20 < 1 + 2 + 4 + 5 + 10 

          2) 40 = 1 + 2 + 4 + 5 + 8 + 10 + 20

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Deficient number]

Sum of the factors of the input (Excluding input) < input

Example., 1) 10 > 1 + 2 + 5 

          2) 15 = 1 + 3 + 5

—————————————––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

[Mersenne number]

Number which contains 1's continuously without 0's starting to ending of a binary representation

Example., 

11       = 3 
111      = 7 
1111     = 15
11111    = 31 
111111   = 63 
1111111  = 127 

if input == ( 2ⁿ - 1 ) -> [Mersenne number]

